description:
['
Help us build the future of HR, payroll and benefits.
Collage is a technology company that transforms the way Canadians manage HR, payroll and benefits. Our revolutionary products automate painful administration tasks and empower HR leaders with new capabilities, which ultimately makes work-life better for all employees.
We also believe in empowering our own people to do their best work by creating a high-performance, supportive work environment and giving our team the right resources to thrive.
Collage was acquired by People Corporation in late 2019 and is on an exciting growth trajectory, offering the ideal balance between a high-growth tech environment and the stability of a larger public company.

Learn more about us at\xa0collage.co.

You will be responsible for:

Creating intuitive, useful and adapted new features and improve upon existing ones;
Working with our product and design teams to understand customer pain points, come up with solutions, and then iterate, and launch daily;
Using your extensive knowledge to build and improve the application;
Actively participating in code reviews and sprint planning;
Building reusable code and libraries for future use;
Optimizing the application for maximum performance, speed, and scalability;
Building reusable code and libraries for future use;
Implementing security and data protection;
Designing and building new platform integrations that drive our product.

You should have:

At least 5 years of experience working as a Software Engineer or Developer at another technology company;
Ability to program in a variety of languages &amp; frameworks (React);
Experience working with AWS;
Experience with PostgreSQL;
Understanding of fundamental design principles behind a scalable application;
Solid knowledge of software engineering, including architecture and algorithms;
Ability to write well-structured, easily maintainable, well-documented code;
Proficient understanding of Git or other version control systems.

We're looking for people who are motivated by:

Learning new technical skills, technologies, or capabilities that can benefit personal and your team’s performance;
Finding solutions to difficult technical challenges;
Taking ownership and knowing that you're contributing to the growth of a product and early-stage company.
            ']

